USENIX SUMMER 1994 TECHNICAL CONFERENCE
June 6-10, 1994
Boston Marriott Copley Place
Boston, Massachusetts

Come join us in celebrating the 25th Anniversary of the UNIX System!
Sponsored by USENIX, the UNIX and Advanced Computing Systems 
	Professional and Technical Association

This posting contains important information about the USENIX Summer 1994
Technical Conference, including:
----Technical sessions program
----Conference Organizers
----Conference schedule of activities and events
----Special hotel and airfare rates -- how to make your reservations
----Fun things to do in Boston
----How to register for the conference
----USENIX membership information
----Conference Registration Form
****FOR COMPLETE TUTORIAL DESCRIPTIONS, Refer to second posting, or
    access our automatic mailserver (directions at end of this
    posting).

Emphasis at the USENIX Conference in Boston is on UNIX and other open
systems and their support of real-world applications.  Presentations
will analyze problem areas and draw important solutions from practical
experience and the results of the latest research.  We'll be taking a
critical look at operating system and related technologies with respect
to the resources and applications that will drive computing in the
1990s.  And, we'll celebrate the first 25 years of the UNIX system, as
we look forward to the next 25!

