THE GURU IS IN
Have a question that's been bothering you?  Try asking a USENIX
guru!   Noted experts from the USENIX community will be available to
answer questions and spark controversy.  These are not presentations,
rather an opportunity for discussion among participants, one more way
to transmit information at the conference.  Please contact The Guru is
IN Coordinator Ed Gould via e-mail to ed@pa.dec.com if you would like
to volunteer your expertise for a session.

WORK-IN-PROGRESS REPORTS
Short, pithy and fun, Work-in-Progress (WIP) Reports introduce
interesting new or ongoing work.  If you have interesting work you
would like to share or a cool idea that is not ready to be published, a
WIP Report is for you!  WIPs are scheduled within the technical
sessions program and you will enjoy the insightful feedback you receive
to your ideas.  We are particularly interested in presenting student
work.  To reserve your presentation slot, contact Peg Schafer via
e-mail to wips@usenix.org

BIRDS-OF-A-FEATHER SESSIONS
The always popular Birds-of-a-Feather sessions (BOFs) are very informal
gatherings of persons interested in a particular topic.  BOFs often
feature presentations or demonstrations followed by discussion,
announcements, and the sharing of strategies.  BOFs are offered
Tuesday, Wednesday, and Thursday evenings of the conference.  BOFs may
be scheduled at the conference.  We prefer you schedule BOFs in advance
by telephone to the USENIX Conference Office at 1-714-588-8649 or via
e-mail to conference@usenix.org

RECEPTION
You are invited to join in the fun, mingle with old and new friends,
and enjoy the plentiful hors d'oeuvres and beverages.  The USENIX
Reception is Thursday, June 9, 7:00-9:00 pm.  The Reception is included
in the technical sessions registration fee.  Additional Reception
tickets may be purchased at the conference.

WELCOMING RECEPTION
The Welcoming Reception, Sunday June 5, 6:00-8:00 pm, in the Conference
Registration area offers you a chance to say hello over soft drinks and
snacks.

KICKOFF
The Kickoff introduces attendees to conference events and to Boston.
Kickoff immediately follows the Welcoming Reception on Sunday evening
at 8:00 pm.

TERMINAL ROOM
The USENIX Terminal Room in the Boston Marriott Copley Place will be
open throughout the conference week.  Internet and dial-out access will
be provided.  Copying facilities will be available to create tapes of
miscellaneous GNU and public domain software.  (Look for details posted
to comp.org.usenix)

ATTENDEE MESSAGE SERVICE

Electronic message service will be available Monday, June 6
through noon, Friday, June 10.  Electronic messages to conference
attendees should be addressed: first_lastname@conference.usenix.org

Telephone messages may be left by telephoning the Marriott Copley Place
at 1-617-236-5800 and asking for the USENIX Message Desk extension.
The Message Desk will be open Sunday, June 5, 4:00-9:00 pm, and
continue to be open during conference hours until Friday, June 10 at
3:00 pm.

VENDOR DISPLAY
On Wednesday, June 8, noon-5:00 pm, and Thursday, June 9, 10:00 am-2:00
pm, the USENIX Vendor Display will provide a relaxed environment in
which you can "kick the tires" of important software, hardware and
networking products and discuss needed services.  Emphasis is on
serious answers from technically savvy vendor representatives, so
you'll know how something will work with what you've already got.
Plus, you can review the newest releases from technical and
professional publishers.

Vendors:  The Vendor Display is an exceptional opportunity for
receiving feedback on new development from USENIX's astute attendees.
If your company would like to participate, please contact:  Peter Mui:
1-510-528-8649; FAX:  1-510-548-5738; e-mail: display@usenix.org


