**Special Note:  USENIX Conference Meeting Space
The week-long USENIX conference places a heavy demand on meeting
space.  To offset the cost of meeting space, USENIX guarantees to a
hotel (or hotels) a minimum number of sleeping rooms rented by
attendees.  The hotels then provide meeting space and other services at
no direct cost to USENIX.  Such agreements are complicated and, by
necessity, signed as much as five years in advance.  Contracts contain
penalty clauses (which may exceed $50,000!) if the room guarantee is
unmet.  Moreover, groups that can't live up to their contracts find in
the future they have trouble renting space.  We try to choose sites
that balance easy access, desireable location, and less expensive room
rates.

